Just was put this out there..

snippet.textDisplay:
Honestly I am going to sound odd but I kind of feel sad these bad events change you, somewhat drastically. Don't let the worst people turn you down a different path. You just keep going as far as you can but always leave other routes open when you need them.


I specifically feel sad he seems to infer about giving away his rewards. Like the play buttons and perhaps even a lot of community made stuff like the 100 million button.

In regards to people who enjoy Felix getting robbed, sure he might have more than you, but he had worked for it as much as anyone else by being who he is, and has had to sacrifice so much while us fans can be really mean to him just for the sake of a internet personality. (not trying to sound demeaning there).


Bastards.

snippet.textDisplay: Ultimately, the philosophy of Diogenes is immature. An unsustainable way of life that leaves no heir and little to no benefit to his family or community. The wisdom he leaves is thankfulness, you can do great things with very little. Be thankful for life and what you have.
